An inquest docket has been opened to determine the circumstances around the deaths of four people, burnt beyond recognition in a house fire in Claridge on Monday morning. According to a police source, the Mvoti Fire Department was called to attend to a house fire near the KwaSizabantu Mission in Claridge at around 1am this morning. While putting out the fire, fire fighters made the discovery of four bodies, burnt beyond recognition. It is alleged a security guard alerted the fire department to the fire. Community members from the close knit neighbourhood had already gathered to help put out the flames. Saps confirmed the bodies had been transported to the mortuary, where autopsies will be done. An inquest has been opened to determine the cause of death and the circumstances surrounding the deaths.